trySetState

public boolean trySetState(java.lang.String state)
Returns true if the proposed new given state can be applied. This method do not change the current value of the state, but it is used to verify if the proposed new state is applicable.

A returned false means that the state transition from the current value to the given one is not valid.

Specified by:
trySetState in interface javax.oss.cbe.datatypes.State
Parameters:
state - the new proposed state value
Returns:
true if the transition to this new state is valid, false otherwise.
